| title      = Baidu: 囧
| publisher  = Baike.baidu.com
| accessdate = March 14, 2013
</ref> is also used in the Chinese computing community for a frowning face.<ref>cite web
| url         = http://tv.people.com.cn/BIG5/61602/7815716.html
| title       = 生僻字大行其道 "囧"衍生出各種表情
| work        = People's Daily
| accessdate  = March 14, 2013
| deadurl     = yes
| archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20111007082939/http://tv.people.com.cn/BIG5/61602/7815716.html
| archivedate = October 7, 2011
</ref> It is also combined with posture emoticon Orz, such as 囧rz. The character existed in Oracle bone script, but its use as emoticon was documented as early as January 20, 2005.<ref name="nownews-56E7">cite web
| url         = http://www.nownews.com/2005/01/20/327-1744028.htm
